It will be a mostly cool day ahead, with light rain in places in the east on Tuesday. Otherwise, it will be warmer in places in the west. Temperatures along the coast will be cool to warm, according to the South African Weather Service. The weather in your region Gauteng will be partly cloudy and cool. The expected UVB sunburn index will be high. Mpumalanga will be cloudy and cool, with fog and drizzle over the escarpment. It will become partly in the south from the afternoon. It will be cloudy in the eastern parts of Limpopo, with morning fog and drizzle over the escarpment. Otherwise, it will be partly cloudy and cool but warm over the south-west. The North West will be fine and warm but cool in the south-east. It will be cloudy with fog patches in the eastern parts of the Free State at first. Otherwise, it will be fine and cool but cold in the extreme east. The Northern Cape will be fine and cool to warm. Morning frost is expected over the southern interior. The wind along the coast will be strong. Morning frost is expected in places over the Central Karoo of the Western Cape. Otherwise, it will be fine and cool but warm in places over the interior. The wind along the coast will be moderate. The expected UVB sunburn index will be moderate. The Eastern Cape is expected to be fine and cool but partly cloudy along the coast and adjacent interior. The wind along the coast will be moderate to fresh. It will be cloudy in the northern parts of KwaZulu-Natal. Light rain is expected over the extreme north-east. Otherwise, it will be partly cloudy and cool. It will become fine in the afternoon. The wind along the coast will be moderate to fresh. The expected UVB sunburn index will be moderate.  Click here to see the specific forecast for your city over the next few days